1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,632 --> 00:01:36,392
(Two years ago)

3
00:01:36,392 --> 00:01:37,896
How long have you been working here?

4
00:01:38,392 --> 00:01:39,312
It's been two years.

5
00:01:40,593 --> 00:01:41,233
Have you fit in?

6
00:01:42,593 --> 00:01:43,433
Pretty much.

7
00:01:45,353 --> 00:01:45,993
That's good.

8
00:01:46,713 --> 00:01:49,832
Our company's business volume
is among the top in the industry.

9
00:01:51,552 --> 00:01:52,353
So,

10
00:01:52,953 --> 00:01:54,272
do you have any plans?

11
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:57,552
I just want to work on more projects

12
00:01:58,873 --> 00:02:00,433
and gain more experience

13
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:03,593
to grow a bit faster.

14
00:02:15,112 --> 00:02:15,872
I like you.

15
00:02:16,753 --> 00:02:17,633
Don't do this.

16
00:02:27,712 --> 00:02:30,633
I'm telling you, I've already
complained to HR Department.

17
00:02:31,753 --> 00:02:32,753
It's really unbearable.

18
00:02:33,712 --> 00:02:35,552
He seems perfectly normal usually,

19
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:38,392
working on projects worth tens
or hundreds of millions every day.

20
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:40,473
Turns out he is so bad in private.

21
00:02:42,633 --> 00:02:46,353
Aren't you dressing like this
every day just trying to seduce men?

22
00:02:48,753 --> 00:02:49,552
I...

23
00:02:57,753 --> 00:02:59,112
If you resign voluntarily,

24
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:01,753
the company may
offer you an extra month's severance.

25
00:03:02,392 --> 00:03:04,633
That way, you can find a new job sooner.

26
00:03:05,592 --> 00:03:06,592
If you don't,

27
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:09,592
when your contract expires
in three months,

28
00:03:10,392 --> 00:03:11,793
we won't renew it.

29
00:03:15,913 --> 00:03:17,392
Did Mr. Tang ask you to do this?

30
00:03:17,672 --> 00:03:18,592
Of course not.

31
00:03:29,256 --> 00:03:31,304
(Party B's Signature)

32
00:03:37,872 --> 00:03:38,832
What should I do?

33
00:03:40,233 --> 00:03:41,272
The festival is coming up,

34
00:03:41,272 --> 00:03:42,872
but I haven't found a job yet.

35
00:03:45,793 --> 00:03:48,073
Why is finding a job so hard these days?

36
00:03:49,272 --> 00:03:49,992
So,

37
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:51,592
how could you be so impulsive,

38
00:03:51,832 --> 00:03:52,953
quitting just like that?

39
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:59,233
(I couldn't get any sense of security
from my boyfriend when I was young,)

40
00:04:00,552 --> 00:04:02,152
(overwhelmed by fears of unworthiness.)

41
00:04:08,616 --> 00:04:14,376
(Dependency isn't love,
it's just possession.)

42
00:04:14,376 --> 00:04:18,342
=Episode 17=
(Lifeline)

43
00:04:18,553 --> 00:04:19,712
The Best Employee Award

44
00:04:19,873 --> 00:04:21,073
went to Qiao Hailun.

45
00:04:35,432 --> 00:04:38,617
(List of Winners)

46
00:04:55,832 --> 00:04:57,352
(You didn't invite her to lunch.)

47
00:05:04,152 --> 00:05:05,113
(I couldn't.)

48
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:07,032
(Tao and Lin Sai will come too.)

49
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:09,032
(If they meet, they'll fight.)

50
00:05:09,352 --> 00:05:10,673
(Then send an address later.)

51
00:05:11,032 --> 00:05:11,832
(Meet up quietly.)

52
00:05:21,993 --> 00:05:22,832
Welcome.

53
00:05:28,032 --> 00:05:28,993
16.5 yuan.

54
00:05:28,993 --> 00:05:29,712
Heat this, please.

55
00:05:29,712 --> 00:05:30,113
Okay.

56
00:05:32,673 --> 00:05:35,113
16.5 yuan is received via Alipay.

57
00:05:36,873 --> 00:05:37,633
Welcome.

58
00:05:39,944 --> 00:05:42,824
(November 16, Cao Lei's birthday)

59
00:05:43,032 --> 00:05:44,313
24.5 yuan.

60
00:05:44,792 --> 00:05:45,433
Okay, thanks.

61
00:05:47,073 --> 00:05:48,152
Your food is ready.

62
00:05:53,472 --> 00:05:54,313
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

63
00:06:01,832 --> 00:06:02,433
Come on.

64
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:03,232
Happy birthday!

65
00:06:03,232 --> 00:06:04,193
Happy birthday!

66
00:06:04,633 --> 00:06:06,032
Another year older. Thanks.

67
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:07,392
May you succeed, handsome guy!

68
00:06:08,073 --> 00:06:09,392
May you get better.

69
00:06:09,832 --> 00:06:10,873
You guys eat.

70
00:06:10,873 --> 00:06:11,712
- Okay.
- Okay.

71
00:06:22,073 --> 00:06:23,633
Qiao Hailun is pathetic.

72
00:06:24,953 --> 00:06:26,313
Since she hooked up with Mr. Li,

73
00:06:26,313 --> 00:06:28,073
she's even changed her underwear style.

74
00:06:28,472 --> 00:06:29,193
Really?

75
00:06:29,352 --> 00:06:29,953
Yes, really!

76
00:06:30,553 --> 00:06:33,592
I actually think
Qiao Hailun is pretty pitiful.

77
00:06:34,113 --> 00:06:36,873
Look, what good is sleeping with Mr. Li?

78
00:06:37,113 --> 00:06:38,673
She was still sent to a hilly area.

79
00:06:38,873 --> 00:06:40,352
But she got the Best Employee Award.

80
00:06:40,993 --> 00:06:42,073
So what?

81
00:06:42,073 --> 00:06:43,032
She won't get promoted.

82
00:06:43,993 --> 00:06:44,792
You know what?

83
00:06:45,073 --> 00:06:46,912
I know the Kangya project very well.

84
00:06:47,232 --> 00:06:48,592
It was extremely tough.

85
00:06:48,993 --> 00:06:52,073
Those veterans at Kangya never wanted
to use a consulting firm.

86
00:06:52,073 --> 00:06:53,113
So they didn't cooperate.

87
00:06:53,553 --> 00:06:54,712
It was hard to meet them.

88
00:06:55,193 --> 00:06:56,073
They all played dumb

89
00:06:56,073 --> 00:06:57,313
when you asked about something.

90
00:06:57,873 --> 00:06:59,193
When Qiao Hailun got there,

91
00:06:59,193 --> 00:07:01,193
she was basically crying every day.

92
00:07:02,553 --> 00:07:03,832
Oh, right, they have a hotel.

93
00:07:04,553 --> 00:07:05,953
That hotel's built on a mountain.

94
00:07:05,953 --> 00:07:07,873
Getting in and out
almost relies on steps.

95
00:07:08,113 --> 00:07:09,832
When it rains,
it gets extremely slippery.

96
00:07:10,592 --> 00:07:11,392
My friend told me

97
00:07:11,392 --> 00:07:13,352
that Qiao Hailun fell
on her very first day there.

98
00:07:13,753 --> 00:07:14,832
She almost lost her life.

99
00:07:15,193 --> 00:07:16,313
She deserved it.

100
00:07:16,673 --> 00:07:17,633
Glad to hear that.

101
00:07:25,953 --> 00:07:28,792
Well, today's my birthday.

102
00:07:29,513 --> 00:07:30,753
I meant to invite you,

103
00:07:31,193 --> 00:07:32,753
but I thought you were busy.

104
00:07:33,673 --> 00:07:34,633
Come over and sit down.

105
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:36,392
Waiter, bring an extra dining set.

106
00:07:36,633 --> 00:07:37,232
Don't bother.

107
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:41,633
Headphones for you.
Hope you'll like them.

108
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:43,513
Happy birthday.

109
00:07:43,792 --> 00:07:44,433
Qiao Hailun.

110
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:45,232
Let me explain.

111
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:46,633
No need. I heard everything.

112
00:07:47,873 --> 00:07:48,953
I just want to ask you all.

113
00:07:49,873 --> 00:07:51,193
When you gossip behind my back,

114
00:07:51,673 --> 00:07:52,832
do you feel better?

115
00:07:53,513 --> 00:07:54,152
Probably not.

116
00:08:00,753 --> 00:08:01,873
Sit down.

117
00:08:02,113 --> 00:08:03,513
Sit. Come on.

118
00:08:18,792 --> 00:08:21,113
I've only slept for two hours
over the past couple of days.

119
00:08:21,113 --> 00:08:22,993
You've been doing this
for over a week now.

120
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:26,313
Including today,
it's been exactly half a month.

121
00:08:26,753 --> 00:08:27,873
Don't work too hard.

122
00:08:29,193 --> 00:08:30,313
I can't afford to slow down.

123
00:08:30,673 --> 00:08:33,553
Whether alive or dead,
I belong to Ruijin.

124
00:08:35,553 --> 00:08:36,872
Got a call. Let's go.

125
00:08:46,953 --> 00:08:48,472
(Mr. Li, are you busy?)
(I know I've made mistakes.)

126
00:08:49,592 --> 00:08:51,313
(But I don't think I deserve this.)

127
00:08:52,313 --> 00:08:53,553
(I don't know what to do.)

128
00:08:55,472 --> 00:08:57,313
(I can't wait to see Li Dongming.)

129
00:08:58,752 --> 00:08:59,832
(As long as he's here,)

130
00:09:00,512 --> 00:09:01,913
(those who mock me)

131
00:09:02,112 --> 00:09:03,232
(and look down on me)

132
00:09:03,953 --> 00:09:05,393
(will all become clowns.)

133
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:07,793
(Only Li Dongming can help me.)

134
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:38,232
(Do you have a moment?)

135
00:10:15,273 --> 00:10:15,872
(Hello,)

136
00:10:16,393 --> 00:10:18,752
(the subscriber you dialed is busy.)

137
00:10:18,913 --> 00:10:20,592
(Please try again later.)

138
00:10:20,793 --> 00:10:22,153
You left work early today.

139
00:10:22,832 --> 00:10:23,673
It's the weekend.

140
00:10:23,673 --> 00:10:24,953
I left right after the boss.

141
00:10:25,313 --> 00:10:26,433
How's the place?

142
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:27,673
It's good.

143
00:10:27,673 --> 00:10:28,953
There are lots of handsome guys.

144
00:10:28,953 --> 00:10:29,592
Really?

145
00:10:29,793 --> 00:10:30,393
Let's go.

146
00:10:33,673 --> 00:10:35,153
How many people tonight?

147
00:10:35,592 --> 00:10:36,313
Seven, I think.

148
00:10:36,953 --> 00:10:38,073
No. Eight people.

149
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:39,673
Xiaolou is coming too.

150
00:10:39,872 --> 00:10:41,193
And Yunyun. That makes nine.

151
00:10:41,472 --> 00:10:43,592
Can our reservation fit nine people?

152
00:10:43,953 --> 00:10:44,793
We'll squeeze in.

153
00:10:44,793 --> 00:10:46,872
It's too late to change it now.

154
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:49,153
True. It's Friday.

155
00:10:49,193 --> 00:10:50,632
We're lucky to get a reservation.

156
00:10:51,313 --> 00:10:51,953
Exactly.

157
00:10:58,433 --> 00:10:59,953
If you have time,

158
00:10:59,953 --> 00:11:01,673
go check the office buildings near you.

159
00:11:01,673 --> 00:11:04,313
Or the women's restroom
on the first floor of any mall.

160
00:11:04,673 --> 00:11:06,632
You'll see exactly what I described.

161
00:11:15,553 --> 00:11:16,313
Are you done?

162
00:11:19,673 --> 00:11:20,712
Year-end sales.

163
00:11:22,273 --> 00:11:23,553
I want to tell you something.

164
00:11:26,913 --> 00:11:29,193
I have a friend
who's in the fragrance business.

165
00:11:29,832 --> 00:11:32,352
He designs scents
for different environments.

166
00:11:33,393 --> 00:11:35,553
(Subrose)
We use the scents in our bathroom.

167
00:11:35,673 --> 00:11:36,632
It's called Momili.

168
00:11:37,193 --> 00:11:39,793
When he started out, he needed funding.

169
00:11:40,193 --> 00:11:41,712
I helped him secure an investment

170
00:11:41,712 --> 00:11:43,673
and took a three percent of shares.

171
00:11:44,953 --> 00:11:48,232
Late last year,
his company developed a new system,

172
00:11:48,913 --> 00:11:51,673
combining AI with fragrance design.

173
00:11:52,313 --> 00:11:55,433
Then a big company noticed
his company and wanted to acquire it.

174
00:11:56,033 --> 00:11:57,472
They're almost done negotiating.

175
00:11:58,472 --> 00:12:00,273
The current valuation is 530 million.

176
00:12:00,913 --> 00:12:03,673
So my three percent
would be worth over 15 million.

177
00:12:04,273 --> 00:12:05,033
My friend said

178
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:06,953
that if I want to cash out my shares,

179
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:08,393
he can help me.

180
00:12:14,472 --> 00:12:15,112
What's wrong?

181
00:12:19,313 --> 00:12:19,832
Nothing.

182
00:12:21,313 --> 00:12:22,393
It's just unexpected.

183
00:12:23,313 --> 00:12:25,153
You never mentioned it before.

184
00:12:26,313 --> 00:12:27,953
That happened years ago,

185
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,953
back before we got married.

186
00:12:30,673 --> 00:12:32,832
If it weren't for this acquisition,

187
00:12:33,153 --> 00:12:34,352
I would've forgotten it.

188
00:12:35,953 --> 00:12:37,313
So what should we do

189
00:12:37,313 --> 00:12:39,073
with all that money?

190
00:12:44,153 --> 00:12:45,352
How about buying a house?

191
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:47,472
You've always wanted one with a yard.

192
00:12:47,712 --> 00:12:49,393
Let's buy a house with a yard.

193
00:12:50,913 --> 00:12:52,193
Oh, my!

194
00:12:53,073 --> 00:12:56,793
The company put Dong Yue
in charge of direct store sales.

195
00:12:58,953 --> 00:13:01,193
Didn't Tang Lide manage that before?

196
00:13:01,393 --> 00:13:02,433
Yes.

197
00:13:02,673 --> 00:13:04,553
I was hoping to take that over myself.

198
00:13:04,553 --> 00:13:06,393
I didn't expect Dong Yue to act so fast.

199
00:13:08,712 --> 00:13:09,953
I need to reconsider my plan.

200
00:13:10,673 --> 00:13:11,553
What should I do now?

201
00:13:14,953 --> 00:13:16,872
(I've never seen Li Dongming like this,)

202
00:13:17,752 --> 00:13:20,953
(creating distance with politeness,
and masking arrogance with humility.)

203
00:13:22,112 --> 00:13:23,472
(When was he ever this panicked?)

204
00:13:24,592 --> 00:13:27,512
(But I wasn't as gleeful
as I thought I'd be.)

205
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:29,913
(Perhaps in the face of life itself,)

206
00:13:30,512 --> 00:13:35,832
(all those feelings, love,
and marriage seem insignificant.)

207
00:13:38,313 --> 00:13:39,752
(I suddenly stopped hating him.)

208
00:13:40,793 --> 00:13:42,512
(Instead, I pity him.)

209
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:46,472
(For someone like Li Dongming,
who's inherently arrogant,)

210
00:13:46,752 --> 00:13:48,632
(if he knew I pitied him,)

211
00:13:48,632 --> 00:13:51,793
(he'd probably die of rage
before the cancer even got him.)

212
00:13:52,673 --> 00:13:53,793
(Stop it, Zhao Mei.)

213
00:13:54,872 --> 00:13:55,848
(Can't think that way.)

214
00:13:57,273 --> 00:13:57,872
(Be kind.)

215
00:13:59,496 --> 00:14:00,488
♪Open the window♪

216
00:14:00,488 --> 00:14:01,673
♪See the beautiful night♪

217
00:14:01,673 --> 00:14:02,662
♪Watch the meteor
streaking across the night sky♪

218
00:14:02,662 --> 00:14:03,824
♪Without hesitation♪

219
00:14:03,824 --> 00:14:05,243
♪The clock ticks away♪

220
00:14:05,243 --> 00:14:06,359
♪Relentlessly urging me♪

221
00:14:06,359 --> 00:14:07,112
♪Declined every party♪

222
00:14:07,112 --> 00:14:08,657
♪Living like a compass♪

223
00:14:08,657 --> 00:14:10,377
♪Can't escape paying rent and utilities♪

224
00:14:10,377 --> 00:14:12,822
♪Countless expenses burning up♪

225
00:14:12,822 --> 00:14:13,964
♪But you know♪

226
00:14:13,964 --> 00:14:15,056
♪Pressure upon opening my eyes♪

227
00:14:15,056 --> 00:14:16,480
♪Maybe it fuels me♪

228
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,274
♪The meals eaten on time♪

229
00:14:17,274 --> 00:14:18,067
♪Work can't stop♪

230
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:18,951
♪This game♪

231
00:14:18,951 --> 00:14:20,305
♪Please don't love so hard♪

232
00:14:20,305 --> 00:14:21,436
♪I give up♪

233
00:14:21,436 --> 00:14:22,653
♪Don't fight with yourself♪

234
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:23,973
♪Life isn't a battle♪

235
00:14:23,973 --> 00:14:25,192
♪On being a hero♪

236
00:14:25,192 --> 00:14:26,022
♪No one helps me out♪

237
00:14:26,153 --> 00:14:27,193
Ms. Qiao, you're back.

238
00:14:28,793 --> 00:14:29,472
Ms. Qiao.

239
00:14:30,193 --> 00:14:30,673
Ms. Qiao.

240
00:14:32,004 --> 00:14:33,269
♪You've poured out♪

241
00:14:33,269 --> 00:14:35,534
♪All your sorrow♪

242
00:14:36,313 --> 00:14:38,153
Are you okay?

243
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,112
I'm fine.

244
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:03,404
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

245
00:15:07,816 --> 00:15:10,167
♪Too much of shame♪

246
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:12,193
(It's been almost a week.)

247
00:15:12,872 --> 00:15:14,472
(Li Dongming hasn't come to the office.)

248
00:15:15,193 --> 00:15:16,352
(He doesn't return messages)

249
00:15:16,512 --> 00:15:17,632
(or answer calls.)

250
00:15:18,193 --> 00:15:19,472
(I've heard some executives)

251
00:15:19,472 --> 00:15:22,193
(disappear off the face of the earth
when they resign.)

252
00:15:22,592 --> 00:15:23,553
(No farewells.)

253
00:15:23,553 --> 00:15:24,553
(Just stop showing up.)

254
00:15:25,673 --> 00:15:26,832
(I fear he will do that.)

255
00:15:27,632 --> 00:15:30,793
(Several times, I've wanted
to rush to his place to find him.)

256
00:15:31,832 --> 00:15:32,712
(But I know)

257
00:15:33,752 --> 00:15:36,793
(there's no future
for Li Dongming and me.)

258
00:15:39,016 --> 00:15:41,022
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

259
00:15:41,022 --> 00:15:46,088
♪And I see them sparkling♪

260
00:15:46,088 --> 00:15:48,267
♪Nobody knows♪

261
00:15:48,267 --> 00:15:50,827
♪What tomorrow brings♪

262
00:15:50,827 --> 00:15:53,384
♪You made it through the worst♪

263
00:15:53,384 --> 00:15:55,610
♪The best is yet to come♪

264
00:15:55,610 --> 00:15:59,191
♪The best is yet to come♪

265
00:15:59,191 --> 00:16:06,354
♪Isn't it magical♪

266
00:16:11,793 --> 00:16:12,553
You're fine.

267
00:16:13,073 --> 00:16:15,073
Probably the medicine you took
affected your test.

268
00:16:15,673 --> 00:16:16,872
You're fine. Don't worry.

269
00:16:17,673 --> 00:16:19,673
Just be more careful
with your diet from now on.

270
00:16:21,273 --> 00:16:22,600
Do exercise. Don't stay up late.

271
00:16:24,153 --> 00:16:25,033
Are you sure?

272
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,793
Yeah, you're good.

273
00:16:29,472 --> 00:16:30,193
I...

274
00:16:30,592 --> 00:16:31,153
Honey,

275
00:16:31,512 --> 00:16:32,472
I just saw the doctor.

276
00:16:32,913 --> 00:16:34,393
All the indicators are normal.

277
00:16:34,793 --> 00:16:35,592
That's great news!

278
00:16:36,073 --> 00:16:37,313
Let's celebrate tonight.

279
00:16:37,313 --> 00:16:38,553
At home, I'll cook.

280
00:16:39,153 --> 00:16:41,832
Having breakfast together
at home feels wonderful.

281
00:16:42,872 --> 00:16:43,512
Okay.

282
00:16:43,512 --> 00:16:44,553
I'm in a meeting now.

283
00:16:44,913 --> 00:16:45,793
We'll talk later.

284
00:16:52,112 --> 00:16:54,553
(Good. Got him back again.)

285
00:16:59,033 --> 00:16:59,793
Hello, Mr. Li.

286
00:16:59,913 --> 00:17:00,352
Hello.

287
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:02,033
Dongming.

288
00:17:02,033 --> 00:17:02,553
Wang.

289
00:17:02,553 --> 00:17:04,913
- I haven't seen you these days.
- I was on a business trip.

290
00:17:05,072 --> 00:17:05,752
Busy man.

291
00:17:06,312 --> 00:17:07,433
I'll buy you a coffee later.

292
00:17:08,072 --> 00:17:09,193
I have a favor to ask.

293
00:17:09,193 --> 00:17:09,833
Anytime.

294
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:10,272
Okay.

295
00:17:10,472 --> 00:17:11,272
I'll message you.

296
00:17:11,992 --> 00:17:12,712
Hello, Mr. Li.

297
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:13,472
Hello.

298
00:17:16,433 --> 00:17:17,272
Hello, Mr. Li.

299
00:17:17,913 --> 00:17:19,032
Hello. You are?

300
00:17:19,712 --> 00:17:21,072
I'm the new intern.

301
00:17:21,072 --> 00:17:21,953
My name is Jian An.

302
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:23,472
Come on in.

303
00:17:23,472 --> 00:17:23,873
Okay.

304
00:17:25,193 --> 00:17:26,152
What can I do for you?

305
00:17:26,552 --> 00:17:28,032
It's my first day today.

306
00:17:28,072 --> 00:17:29,072
I brought you bubble tea.

307
00:17:30,512 --> 00:17:31,272
Thank you.

308
00:17:31,913 --> 00:17:35,072
I heard so many stories
about you during training.

309
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:36,833
You're really amazing.

310
00:17:37,593 --> 00:17:39,472
Your work on the GST project shocked me.

311
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:42,072
You actually pulled it off
under tough circumstances.

312
00:17:42,272 --> 00:17:43,393
As you said,

313
00:17:43,433 --> 00:17:44,193
it's just a story.

314
00:17:44,673 --> 00:17:46,752
Could I ask for your advice
if I have questions?

315
00:17:48,072 --> 00:17:48,512
Sure.

316
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:51,512
Could I add you on WeChat?

317
00:17:53,913 --> 00:17:54,312
Okay.

318
00:18:05,072 --> 00:18:05,633
You may go.

319
00:18:13,272 --> 00:18:14,024
Mr. Li.

320
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,016
Here is the new
Supplemental Agreement from Kangya.

321
00:18:19,992 --> 00:18:20,712
I'll head out now.

322
00:18:39,048 --> 00:18:40,649
(Supplemental Agreement to Kangya Hotel
Management Consulting Agreement)

323
00:18:51,304 --> 00:18:55,016
(Miss you)

324
00:19:10,472 --> 00:19:10,953
Dongming.

325
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:12,232
Sir.

326
00:19:13,512 --> 00:19:14,280
Going to socialize?

327
00:19:14,673 --> 00:19:16,272
No, after meeting a client,

328
00:19:16,272 --> 00:19:17,672
I'll go home to accompany my wife.

329
00:19:18,232 --> 00:19:18,953
Good.

330
00:19:19,752 --> 00:19:21,353
How was your checkup? All good?

331
00:19:21,353 --> 00:19:21,873
It was fine.

332
00:19:22,393 --> 00:19:23,673
Physical health is important.

333
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:26,712
The bosses at our overseas headquarters

334
00:19:27,353 --> 00:19:30,193
value physical health and a happy home

335
00:19:30,792 --> 00:19:31,593
above all.

336
00:19:32,953 --> 00:19:33,312
Right.

337
00:19:33,953 --> 00:19:34,792
Physical health.

338
00:19:35,393 --> 00:19:36,193
A happy home.

339
00:20:42,072 --> 00:20:44,353
Do you remember what I told you earlier?

340
00:20:47,512 --> 00:20:48,193
I do.

341
00:20:49,193 --> 00:20:49,953
You have a family.

342
00:20:51,232 --> 00:20:52,472
Our relationship

343
00:20:55,393 --> 00:20:56,232
means nothing.

344
00:20:58,833 --> 00:20:59,433
Hailun.

345
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:02,433
You and I...

346
00:21:04,873 --> 00:21:06,712
Walls have ears.

347
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:08,712
All these rumors

348
00:21:09,113 --> 00:21:09,992
don't bother me,

349
00:21:10,673 --> 00:21:11,752
but they will hurt you.

350
00:21:12,913 --> 00:21:13,512
I know.

351
00:21:15,193 --> 00:21:16,032
Don't worry, Mr. Li.

352
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:18,512
I'll be careful.

353
00:21:22,992 --> 00:21:23,913
(But what can I do?)

354
00:21:25,232 --> 00:21:26,232
(I can't leave him.)

355
00:21:34,792 --> 00:21:35,193
Hello.

356
00:21:41,353 --> 00:21:42,953
Moonlight City changing room.

357
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:46,032
The latest promotion plan
for Moonlight City.

358
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:47,552
Let's say

359
00:21:48,353 --> 00:21:49,953
on Friday night,
you're going to a party.

360
00:21:50,512 --> 00:21:52,232
Where would you get changed?

361
00:21:52,913 --> 00:21:53,833
The office.

362
00:21:55,992 --> 00:21:58,072
Not every woman has an office.

363
00:21:58,792 --> 00:22:01,673
Most of the time,
they can only choose the restroom.

364
00:22:02,913 --> 00:22:03,353
Now,

365
00:22:03,792 --> 00:22:06,280
if you could provide them
with more comfortable environments,

366
00:22:06,472 --> 00:22:08,593
let's say a room
with curtains and mirrors,

367
00:22:09,472 --> 00:22:10,953
and some Moonlight City champagne,

368
00:22:12,673 --> 00:22:13,232
I bet

369
00:22:13,232 --> 00:22:15,624
they'll take a lot of selfies
with our champagne bottles.

370
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:17,712
Zhao Mei's idea, right?

371
00:22:17,712 --> 00:22:18,232
Yes.

372
00:22:18,752 --> 00:22:21,113
I think it's a very attractive idea.

373
00:22:23,232 --> 00:22:25,712
Maybe she's an attractive person.

374
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:32,752
They slept together?

375
00:22:32,752 --> 00:22:33,752
How would I know?

376
00:22:33,953 --> 00:22:35,472
Where did you get this photo?

377
00:22:35,913 --> 00:22:36,673
Everywhere.

378
00:22:43,393 --> 00:22:44,433
Interesting.

379
00:22:45,193 --> 00:22:46,913
Is this photo real?

380
00:22:47,153 --> 00:22:48,433
Could it be photoshopped?

381
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:49,833
It's real.

382
00:22:49,833 --> 00:22:51,512
I had it verified by professionals.

383
00:22:52,752 --> 00:22:54,193
If it's real,

384
00:22:54,472 --> 00:22:58,593
it means while Ms. Zhao
is publicly competing against Dong Yue,

385
00:22:58,953 --> 00:23:01,673
they're actually doing this privately.

386
00:23:02,673 --> 00:23:03,712
That's disgusting.

387
00:23:04,032 --> 00:23:04,833
It's a fact.

388
00:23:05,593 --> 00:23:06,272
Upscale hotel.

389
00:23:06,272 --> 00:23:07,552
Hao.

390
00:23:08,272 --> 00:23:09,272
Why are you so quiet?

391
00:23:12,272 --> 00:23:14,072
I think this photo looks totally normal.

392
00:23:14,712 --> 00:23:16,512
I don't know
why you're all acting so weird.

393
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:18,232
Normal?

394
00:23:20,512 --> 00:23:25,312
What normal conversation happens
in a hotel room?

395
00:23:25,873 --> 00:23:26,593
Come on.

396
00:23:26,953 --> 00:23:28,193
It's obvious.

397
00:23:29,353 --> 00:23:33,232
But I feel like
you just don't want to face the fact

398
00:23:33,512 --> 00:23:35,633
that Ms. Zhao is having an affair
with Dong Yue.

399
00:23:36,472 --> 00:23:37,113
Right?

400
00:23:40,673 --> 00:23:41,312
Again?

401
00:23:42,393 --> 00:23:43,393
I said

402
00:23:44,153 --> 00:23:45,232
they're having an affair.

403
00:23:45,873 --> 00:23:47,833
You're scared to face the truth.

404
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:48,512
Alright, stop it.

405
00:23:48,873 --> 00:23:49,512
Stop talking.

406
00:23:50,353 --> 00:23:51,673
Hao, that's not what he meant.

407
00:23:51,673 --> 00:23:52,272
Don't be mad.

408
00:23:52,953 --> 00:23:54,153
What will we eat later?

409
00:23:54,153 --> 00:23:54,633
Yeah.

410
00:23:57,416 --> 00:24:00,400
(Did you see it?)

411
00:24:12,472 --> 00:24:14,433
When did you get together with Dong Yue?

412
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:15,873
How come I didn't know about it?

413
00:24:20,673 --> 00:24:22,833
I'm not with him.

414
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:26,032
I just wanted to talk
with him that day after dinner.

415
00:24:26,032 --> 00:24:28,153
There were many people outside,
so we went to a room.

416
00:24:29,752 --> 00:24:31,673
I didn't know who took that picture.

417
00:24:32,113 --> 00:24:34,113
You don't need to explain to me.

418
00:24:34,953 --> 00:24:36,193
I don't mind.

419
00:24:36,393 --> 00:24:38,232
Dong Yue is a catch, right?

420
00:24:38,353 --> 00:24:39,433
What I mind is

421
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:43,193
that you did something big secretly
and didn't even tell me.

422
00:24:43,193 --> 00:24:44,393
I'm with Weiwei and my mom.

423
00:24:44,393 --> 00:24:45,072
I'm hanging up.

424
00:24:45,072 --> 00:24:45,913
Talk later. Bye!

425
00:24:45,913 --> 00:24:46,673
Bye, Mingming.

426
00:24:47,792 --> 00:24:49,833
Mom,
this braised pork rice is delicious!

427
00:24:50,353 --> 00:24:51,433
Of course.

428
00:24:51,992 --> 00:24:52,873
This braised pork

429
00:24:52,873 --> 00:24:55,193
is made with pork collar, pork loin,

430
00:24:55,193 --> 00:24:56,433
and pork belly.

431
00:24:56,433 --> 00:24:57,153
So many!

432
00:24:57,153 --> 00:24:58,673
See the black stuff on top?

433
00:24:58,953 --> 00:25:00,032
That's a black truffle.

434
00:25:00,393 --> 00:25:02,272
That's why
this braised pork rice is expensive.

435
00:25:03,913 --> 00:25:05,193
Mom, this is the monkfish liver.

436
00:25:05,193 --> 00:25:05,752
Have a try.

437
00:25:06,472 --> 00:25:07,153
Alright.

438
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:13,873
It's really tasty!

439
00:25:14,193 --> 00:25:15,512
I absolutely love this dish.

440
00:25:16,593 --> 00:25:20,353
Is your boyfriend footing the bill
for this meal?

441
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:23,153
Since when does Mom have a boyfriend?

442
00:25:24,593 --> 00:25:26,032
What's all the fuss about?

443
00:25:26,232 --> 00:25:26,953
She is pretty.

444
00:25:26,953 --> 00:25:28,393
It's natural to have a boyfriend.

445
00:25:28,712 --> 00:25:30,032
No, not at all.

446
00:25:30,032 --> 00:25:31,512
I told you before there isn't one.

447
00:25:31,712 --> 00:25:32,752
So you got rich?

448
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:36,113
It's an expensive restaurant.

449
00:25:37,153 --> 00:25:37,712
So what?

450
00:25:37,712 --> 00:25:39,312
Can't I treat you to something nice?

451
00:25:39,913 --> 00:25:41,873
I always take clients
to fancy restaurants.

452
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,472
I just want to treat you something nice.

453
00:25:43,472 --> 00:25:45,153
This place uses premium ingredients.

454
00:25:45,633 --> 00:25:46,353
It's delicious.

455
00:25:46,353 --> 00:25:47,512
You have a conscience.

456
00:25:48,593 --> 00:25:49,992
Didn't I have it before?

457
00:25:53,032 --> 00:25:54,433
I'll take you and Weiwei

458
00:25:54,433 --> 00:25:55,633
to buy some new outfits.

459
00:25:55,673 --> 00:25:56,433
Awesome!

460
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:01,673
The outfit you're wearing today

461
00:26:01,953 --> 00:26:06,113
would look even better paired
with your priciest handbag.

462
00:26:10,353 --> 00:26:11,472
I sold that bag.

463
00:26:11,873 --> 00:26:12,712
What?

464
00:26:13,232 --> 00:26:14,232
Smart choice.

465
00:26:14,512 --> 00:26:15,353
It's practical

466
00:26:15,353 --> 00:26:16,712
to sell an expensive bag.

467
00:26:25,113 --> 00:26:26,552
Mom, peel another one for Weiwei.

468
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:28,272
Sure.

469
00:26:31,712 --> 00:26:32,272
(Danning,)

470
00:26:32,552 --> 00:26:34,032
(I reviewed this month's orders.)

471
00:26:34,032 --> 00:26:36,008
(Sales dropped by half
compared to last month.)

472
00:26:36,433 --> 00:26:37,512
I did some digging around.

473
00:26:37,792 --> 00:26:39,633
Some ordered directly through Dong Yue.

474
00:26:40,232 --> 00:26:45,393
Li Longyun from Huijing
ordered two limited-edition Ming Jue.

475
00:26:45,752 --> 00:26:47,433
He placed the order with Dong Yue.

476
00:26:48,232 --> 00:26:51,232
And Mr. Bai from Golden Age
should've placed his order

477
00:26:51,752 --> 00:26:53,552
this month already.

478
00:26:54,032 --> 00:26:55,512
But so far, he hasn't ordered.

479
00:26:56,193 --> 00:26:58,833
Danning, should I try to test him?

480
00:26:59,433 --> 00:27:00,072
No need.

481
00:27:00,512 --> 00:27:01,752
I've got a rough idea of it.

482
00:27:02,072 --> 00:27:02,673
Danning,

483
00:27:03,232 --> 00:27:07,153
did you have a fight with Mr. Shen?

484
00:27:08,833 --> 00:27:11,472
Don't ask questions you shouldn't.

485
00:27:12,752 --> 00:27:14,113
I'll handle the sales issue.

486
00:27:16,153 --> 00:27:16,552
Alright.

487
00:27:29,640 --> 00:27:31,917
(Green chili pepper)

488
00:27:33,633 --> 00:27:34,593
Anything else?

489
00:27:45,256 --> 00:27:47,112
(Moss Cafe)

490
00:27:49,633 --> 00:27:50,232
Hi.

491
00:27:50,833 --> 00:27:52,193
Nice photo.

492
00:27:56,232 --> 00:27:57,472
The photo of Dong Yue and me?

493
00:27:57,953 --> 00:27:58,792
You've seen it?

494
00:27:59,113 --> 00:27:59,873
Yes.

495
00:27:59,873 --> 00:28:01,953
Someone showed it to me
first thing when he came.

496
00:28:10,472 --> 00:28:11,472
You can still smile?

497
00:28:12,712 --> 00:28:13,712
I'd prefer to be serious,

498
00:28:13,712 --> 00:28:16,072
but I've gotten loads
of congratulatory calls.

499
00:28:18,032 --> 00:28:18,833
What?

500
00:28:19,193 --> 00:28:21,953
You know
how they stir up drama out of nothing.

501
00:28:22,232 --> 00:28:25,353
Especially now,
they've got "solid evidence".

502
00:28:26,792 --> 00:28:28,312
That's what puzzles me.

503
00:28:28,792 --> 00:28:31,393
We made a last-minute decision
to return to the hotel that night.

504
00:28:31,633 --> 00:28:33,272
I guess someone was tailing us,

505
00:28:33,272 --> 00:28:35,992
or he couldn't have just camped there,

506
00:28:35,992 --> 00:28:37,272
waiting to snap that photo.

507
00:28:37,712 --> 00:28:39,873
Don't you have
your sense of humor today?

508
00:28:41,633 --> 00:28:42,593
I am a bit on edge.

509
00:28:45,272 --> 00:28:45,792
Sorry.

510
00:28:47,032 --> 00:28:48,032
What for?

511
00:28:48,032 --> 00:28:49,113
You didn't take the photo.

512
00:28:55,072 --> 00:28:56,032
It was you?

513
00:28:56,232 --> 00:28:57,312
Definitely not me.

514
00:28:57,312 --> 00:28:58,752
Why would I photograph myself?

515
00:28:58,992 --> 00:29:00,072
Who knows?

516
00:29:00,953 --> 00:29:03,272
In these scandals,
women always get the short end.

517
00:29:03,992 --> 00:29:06,593
Given our current rivalry,

518
00:29:06,992 --> 00:29:09,673
this could
cloud the boss's judgment of me.

519
00:29:11,472 --> 00:29:15,472
Besides, you're known for playing dirty.

520
00:29:15,552 --> 00:29:17,433
I play dirty?

521
00:29:20,712 --> 00:29:24,472
You steered small distributors
to Barry behind Shen Mo's back.

522
00:29:24,992 --> 00:29:26,752
If that's not playing dirty, what is?

523
00:29:27,792 --> 00:29:29,272
You're well-informed, Ms. Zhao.

524
00:29:29,272 --> 00:29:30,992
Let me guess which distributor it was.

525
00:29:32,353 --> 00:29:33,153
Zhuang Zhiqiang.

526
00:29:35,032 --> 00:29:36,113
You're no different.

527
00:29:36,712 --> 00:29:38,072
You've got insiders in HR, right?

528
00:29:40,472 --> 00:29:41,953
Cai Heping, right?

529
00:29:44,193 --> 00:29:44,792
I was right.

530
00:29:46,833 --> 00:29:48,593
Mr. Dong, good for you.

531
00:29:49,113 --> 00:29:52,032
Even Qi Youlan's trusted subordinate is
on your side.

532
00:29:52,032 --> 00:29:53,353
Let's refocus on the photo issue.

533
00:29:53,353 --> 00:29:53,913
Forget it.

534
00:29:54,353 --> 00:29:54,992
Just let it go.

535
00:29:55,272 --> 00:29:56,792
Denials usually make things worse.

536
00:29:56,792 --> 00:29:57,512
Just let it be.

537
00:29:59,433 --> 00:30:00,193
Well,

538
00:30:00,633 --> 00:30:03,312
since my very first day at GST,

539
00:30:03,833 --> 00:30:06,552
I've been battling rumors and scandals.

540
00:30:06,552 --> 00:30:08,873
After ten years,
I'm still fighting the same thing.

541
00:30:09,752 --> 00:30:10,792
I've heard so many rumors

542
00:30:10,792 --> 00:30:13,272
about you and Xu, Gao Jiawei,

543
00:30:14,032 --> 00:30:15,312
Wang Hao, and...

544
00:30:15,312 --> 00:30:16,232
Wang Hao?

545
00:30:17,633 --> 00:30:19,032
Rumors about Wang Hao and me?

546
00:30:19,032 --> 00:30:19,712
Sure.

547
00:30:20,752 --> 00:30:21,393
Many gossips?

548
00:30:21,752 --> 00:30:22,633
Not really.

549
00:30:22,792 --> 00:30:24,584
Not as many as the rumors
about you and Xu.

550
00:30:26,032 --> 00:30:27,712
Could you please stop upsetting me?

551
00:30:31,193 --> 00:30:32,136
Let me buy you dinner.

552
00:30:34,913 --> 00:30:35,433
No, thanks.

553
00:30:35,752 --> 00:30:36,512
I have to go.

554
00:30:37,433 --> 00:30:38,113
Got a party?

555
00:30:39,193 --> 00:30:41,312
You'd better be ready
to be gossiped about.

556
00:30:42,353 --> 00:30:42,873
No.

557
00:30:45,193 --> 00:30:46,193
Just going home.

558
00:31:12,552 --> 00:31:13,833
Sometimes, I really feel

559
00:31:14,992 --> 00:31:16,232
it's meaningless to live.

560
00:31:18,712 --> 00:31:19,433
For example?

561
00:31:24,833 --> 00:31:25,953
Everything is meaningless.

562
00:31:41,353 --> 00:31:43,992
There are so few ride-hailing cars
at this hour.

563
00:31:43,992 --> 00:31:45,640
The closest one is seven minutes away.

564
00:32:04,792 --> 00:32:05,472
Look,

565
00:32:05,833 --> 00:32:08,232
the double skin milk
from this place is excellent.

566
00:32:08,232 --> 00:32:09,072
You must try it.

567
00:32:27,113 --> 00:32:28,272
If this double skin milk

568
00:32:28,272 --> 00:32:30,792
is combined with our company's Gennadiy,

569
00:32:30,833 --> 00:32:31,953
wouldn't that be great?

570
00:32:31,953 --> 00:32:35,712
Could you not bring up company products
in front of my safe space?

571
00:32:35,712 --> 00:32:36,633
It upsets me.

572
00:32:37,032 --> 00:32:39,072
Okay, I won't mention it.

573
00:32:56,272 --> 00:32:58,633
Let's keep our distance lately.

574
00:33:00,552 --> 00:33:01,433
Lay low a bit.

575
00:33:02,633 --> 00:33:04,393
No need
to give everyone more to talk about.

576
00:33:04,472 --> 00:33:05,113
What do you say?

577
00:33:07,272 --> 00:33:07,752
Fine.

578
00:33:23,153 --> 00:33:23,873
You're back.

579
00:33:28,792 --> 00:33:29,953
Why are you spacing out?

580
00:33:31,312 --> 00:33:33,312
I just think
this scene looks a bit strange.

581
00:33:35,113 --> 00:33:36,633
Don't you find it warm?

582
00:33:38,193 --> 00:33:38,833
Sure.

583
00:33:39,593 --> 00:33:40,792
Hurry up and wash your hands.

584
00:33:41,272 --> 00:33:42,353
Dinner is ready.

585
00:33:42,353 --> 00:33:43,312
We can eat soon.

586
00:33:48,433 --> 00:33:50,992
I have inherited the cooking skill
from my dad.

587
00:33:51,633 --> 00:33:53,232
During our company team-building,

588
00:33:53,433 --> 00:33:55,433
I told them I was a great cook.

589
00:33:55,433 --> 00:33:56,264
They didn't buy it.

590
00:33:56,833 --> 00:33:59,072
I made them a sweet and sour fried egg,

591
00:33:59,312 --> 00:34:00,472
and it totally amazed them.

592
00:34:01,193 --> 00:34:02,433
I said, "What's the big deal?"

593
00:34:02,712 --> 00:34:04,193
"You guys got into university,"

594
00:34:04,792 --> 00:34:06,272
"got into our company,"

595
00:34:06,433 --> 00:34:08,032
"and landed such difficult projects."

596
00:34:08,192 --> 00:34:10,472
"Is cooking harder than that?"

597
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:12,152
"The key is whether you try hard."

598
00:34:17,152 --> 00:34:17,873
Dongming.

599
00:34:18,953 --> 00:34:19,713
Sorry.

600
00:34:19,713 --> 00:34:20,873
You can't cook either.

601
00:34:22,393 --> 00:34:24,313
Let me show you something interesting.

602
00:34:32,552 --> 00:34:34,592
Come on,
let's do it again from this angle.

603
00:34:35,192 --> 00:34:36,552
Excuse me, could you move aside?

604
00:34:37,433 --> 00:34:38,793
Come on, let's start over.

605
00:34:39,273 --> 00:34:41,992
The boss has recovered.

606
00:34:42,192 --> 00:34:44,793
We have to write reports again.

607
00:34:44,793 --> 00:34:48,233
What does Xiao Yang look like?
He looks like a baby, right?

608
00:34:50,552 --> 00:34:51,273
Zhao Mei.

609
00:34:53,833 --> 00:34:56,953
Although my health check
was a close call,

610
00:34:58,433 --> 00:35:00,833
it still served
as a wake-up call for Xiao Yang and me.

611
00:35:03,353 --> 00:35:04,913
It made me rethink a lot of things.

612
00:35:05,713 --> 00:35:08,953
I used to think
work was more important than life.

613
00:35:10,433 --> 00:35:11,512
Xiao Yang is an example.

614
00:35:13,353 --> 00:35:14,233
I got the idea.

615
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:15,912
(Mr. Huang)

616
00:35:20,353 --> 00:35:20,833
Hello?

617
00:35:21,713 --> 00:35:22,713
Sure. Go ahead.

618
00:35:24,833 --> 00:35:25,393
I'm at home.

619
00:35:27,273 --> 00:35:27,873
Sure.

620
00:35:28,433 --> 00:35:29,913
If she doesn't mind, I'll be fine.

621
00:35:31,672 --> 00:35:32,753
Okay, I'll arrange it.

622
00:35:33,353 --> 00:35:34,552
I'll send you the time soon.

623
00:35:35,632 --> 00:35:36,192
See you.

624
00:35:43,273 --> 00:35:45,288
Huang from the Tobacco Group
asked me to play golf.

625
00:35:50,753 --> 00:35:51,353
Zhao Mei.

626
00:35:55,313 --> 00:35:56,353
I have something to say.

627
00:36:01,632 --> 00:36:02,873
Let's have a child.

628
00:36:09,032 --> 00:36:10,072
I'm serious.

629
00:36:12,152 --> 00:36:12,873
Today,

630
00:36:14,112 --> 00:36:16,112
the moment the doctor told me
I was fine,

631
00:36:17,032 --> 00:36:18,433
it felt like I had escaped death.

632
00:36:19,233 --> 00:36:20,512
I suddenly had this thought.

633
00:36:20,992 --> 00:36:22,072
I want a child.

634
00:36:22,233 --> 00:36:23,552
A child with you.

635
00:36:24,393 --> 00:36:26,152
I hope our child is as beautiful as you

636
00:36:26,713 --> 00:36:27,512
and is a girl.

637
00:36:29,632 --> 00:36:30,953
She'll be my sweet girl.

638
00:36:31,873 --> 00:36:34,552
I'll buy her a roomful of nice dresses

639
00:36:34,833 --> 00:36:36,032
and take her around the world.

640
00:36:37,992 --> 00:36:39,393
If we

641
00:36:40,152 --> 00:36:41,833
have a son first,

642
00:36:42,592 --> 00:36:44,833
we'll try harder to have a second child.

643
00:36:44,833 --> 00:36:45,833
I've known everything

644
00:36:48,753 --> 00:36:49,793
about you and Qiao Hailun.

645
00:37:01,273 --> 00:37:02,233
I want a divorce.

646
00:37:11,072 --> 00:37:11,713
No way.

647
00:37:12,433 --> 00:37:14,112
I shouldn't have hooked up with her.

648
00:37:14,112 --> 00:37:16,200
I can make amends.
I promise it won't happen again.

649
00:37:16,472 --> 00:37:17,592
I won't accept a divorce.

650
00:37:18,992 --> 00:37:20,793
My request for divorce isn't an impulse.

651
00:37:21,353 --> 00:37:22,592
I've given it a lot of thought.

652
00:37:24,552 --> 00:37:26,793
You said you found out
about this in Shanghai.

653
00:37:27,233 --> 00:37:28,753
Why did I go to Shanghai at that time?

654
00:37:28,753 --> 00:37:29,552
It was for you.

655
00:37:29,552 --> 00:37:30,393
I went to see Barry.

656
00:37:30,393 --> 00:37:32,152
I reasoned with him,

657
00:37:32,152 --> 00:37:33,672
hoping he would promote you.

658
00:37:33,913 --> 00:37:34,552
I know.

659
00:37:34,552 --> 00:37:36,313
I've always spared no effort for you.

660
00:37:37,273 --> 00:37:37,833
I know.

661
00:37:37,833 --> 00:37:39,112
The other day,

662
00:37:39,313 --> 00:37:41,472
I told you
that Momili was going to be acquired.

663
00:37:42,233 --> 00:37:43,672
I do want to spend my life with you.

664
00:37:43,672 --> 00:37:44,393
I do love you.

665
00:37:44,393 --> 00:37:45,953
Otherwise, would I have told you?

666
00:37:45,953 --> 00:37:47,393
Why would I tell you?

667
00:37:48,112 --> 00:37:48,793
I know.

668
00:37:49,992 --> 00:37:51,152
I've done so much for you.

669
00:37:51,152 --> 00:37:54,032
Can't you give me a chance?

670
00:37:54,032 --> 00:37:54,512
No.

671
00:37:54,873 --> 00:37:55,512
Why?

672
00:37:59,353 --> 00:38:00,753
What if I forgive you this time?

673
00:38:02,393 --> 00:38:03,313
I've thought

674
00:38:03,873 --> 00:38:05,433
about what our life would be like.

675
00:38:05,433 --> 00:38:05,992
Like what?

676
00:38:06,313 --> 00:38:11,152
At first, you'd be very good to me
because you feel guilty.

677
00:38:11,393 --> 00:38:12,992
But you'd also become very careful.

678
00:38:13,632 --> 00:38:17,713
And I would try to forget your mistake.

679
00:38:17,713 --> 00:38:19,753
I would pretend that it never happened.

680
00:38:20,313 --> 00:38:21,433
But after a while,

681
00:38:22,112 --> 00:38:23,873
like six months or a year,

682
00:38:24,512 --> 00:38:26,072
you wouldn't be so careful anymore.

683
00:38:26,353 --> 00:38:28,393
You'd work
and travel on business as usual.

684
00:38:28,833 --> 00:38:30,233
But I wouldn't forget.

685
00:38:30,833 --> 00:38:32,273
I'd become suspicious.

686
00:38:32,273 --> 00:38:34,393
I'd doubt every female colleague
around you.

687
00:38:35,273 --> 00:38:37,192
And once we have an argument,

688
00:38:37,913 --> 00:38:41,072
I'd remember what you did to hurt me.

689
00:38:41,632 --> 00:38:44,353
I couldn't help
but bring up your affair again.

690
00:38:46,313 --> 00:38:48,433
And bringing up the past
would make me seem petty

691
00:38:48,433 --> 00:38:49,833
and unreasonable.

692
00:38:49,873 --> 00:38:51,233
And you'd get angry out of shame.

693
00:38:51,472 --> 00:38:52,393
I wouldn't.

694
00:38:52,393 --> 00:38:52,913
You would.

695
00:38:54,672 --> 00:38:57,353
Debtors hate to see their creditors.

696
00:39:02,393 --> 00:39:05,592
Actually, I don't hate you now.

697
00:39:06,672 --> 00:39:07,873
However,

698
00:39:09,713 --> 00:39:12,873
if your affair was brought up
again and again,

699
00:39:13,393 --> 00:39:15,313
there would be nothing
but hatred between us.

700
00:39:15,713 --> 00:39:17,672
Not only would I hate you,
but you'd hate me too.

701
00:39:17,713 --> 00:39:19,032
And I'd hate myself even more.

702
00:39:19,192 --> 00:39:21,833
I'd regret why I didn't get a divorce
in the first place.

703
00:39:22,273 --> 00:39:23,512
What you said could happen.

704
00:39:23,512 --> 00:39:24,913
But that's only one possibility.

705
00:39:24,913 --> 00:39:27,192
Maybe time will let us forget everything

706
00:39:27,192 --> 00:39:28,632
and completely move on.

707
00:39:30,753 --> 00:39:31,753
I can't do it.

708
00:39:34,192 --> 00:39:35,992
Every time I think of that scene,

709
00:39:37,472 --> 00:39:39,032
I get so angry.

710
00:39:39,353 --> 00:39:41,353
Why do you have to be like this?

711
00:39:42,072 --> 00:39:43,953
You need me, you know?

712
00:39:43,953 --> 00:39:45,713
Why do you
have to block your career path?

713
00:39:45,713 --> 00:39:47,233
You need me.

714
00:39:49,313 --> 00:39:50,592
You mean the promotion?

715
00:39:51,192 --> 00:39:52,592
There's something you didn't know.

716
00:39:52,833 --> 00:39:54,433
Barry really doesn't like you.

717
00:39:54,632 --> 00:39:56,393
You're disobedient and uncontrollable.

718
00:39:56,552 --> 00:39:59,072
What boss would
like a disobedient director?

719
00:39:59,353 --> 00:40:01,393
With my full support, you had the chance

720
00:40:01,393 --> 00:40:03,072
to compete for the director position.

721
00:40:03,472 --> 00:40:05,032
I made a mistake.

722
00:40:05,032 --> 00:40:05,753
I admit it.

723
00:40:06,313 --> 00:40:08,552
But to err is human.

724
00:40:10,833 --> 00:40:12,873
Give me a chance to make amends, okay?

725
00:40:14,433 --> 00:40:15,273
No.

726
00:40:19,393 --> 00:40:21,953
I really don't like what you just said.

727
00:40:22,512 --> 00:40:24,112
Before, you emphasized to me

728
00:40:24,112 --> 00:40:26,793
that Barry promoted me
mainly because I'm a woman.

729
00:40:27,512 --> 00:40:29,112
I don't like that reason either.

730
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:30,833
But I was telling the truth.

731
00:40:32,552 --> 00:40:34,393
It's the truth in your eyes.

732
00:40:34,393 --> 00:40:35,953
It's the truth as you see it.

733
00:40:48,296 --> 00:40:49,472
(Divorce Agreement)

734
00:40:49,472 --> 00:40:51,112
I've prepared the divorce papers.

735
00:40:51,592 --> 00:40:52,233
Zhao Mei, you...

736
00:40:55,552 --> 00:40:58,512
Obviously, today isn't the best time
to resolve this issue.

737
00:40:59,353 --> 00:41:00,953
If you can't get past this mental block,

738
00:41:01,472 --> 00:41:03,273
I can accept a temporary separation.

739
00:41:05,393 --> 00:41:06,953
I hope you can calm down a bit.

740
00:41:23,802 --> 00:41:28,542
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

741
00:41:32,992 --> 00:41:34,912
♪Too much of shame♪

742
00:41:35,258 --> 00:41:38,054
♪To waste it crying♪

743
00:41:40,512 --> 00:41:42,432
♪Leave all behind you♪

744
00:41:42,432 --> 00:41:44,712
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

745
00:41:44,832 --> 00:41:47,061
♪You know how far you've gone♪

746
00:41:47,196 --> 00:41:49,472
♪In the fire you rise again♪

747
00:41:49,658 --> 00:41:52,018
♪You made it through the worst♪

748
00:41:52,156 --> 00:41:54,360
♪The best is yet to come♪

749
00:41:54,603 --> 00:41:56,743
♪The best is yet to come♪

750
00:41:59,445 --> 00:42:00,768
♪Isn't it magical♪

751
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:02,400
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

752
00:42:02,432 --> 00:42:04,899
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

753
00:42:04,899 --> 00:42:07,352
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

754
00:42:07,433 --> 00:42:10,081
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

755
00:42:10,170 --> 00:42:12,701
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

756
00:42:12,781 --> 00:42:15,003
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

757
00:42:15,145 --> 00:42:16,226
♪But I don't want to♪

758
00:42:16,335 --> 00:42:18,601
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

759
00:42:18,717 --> 00:42:19,782
♪Until 3 AM♪

760
00:42:19,953 --> 00:42:21,158
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

761
00:42:21,312 --> 00:42:22,545
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

762
00:42:22,636 --> 00:42:25,000
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

763
00:42:25,147 --> 00:42:29,557
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

764
00:42:44,282 --> 00:42:45,718
♪Leave all behind you♪

765
00:42:45,822 --> 00:42:48,309
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

766
00:42:48,492 --> 00:42:50,621
♪You know how far you've gone♪

767
00:42:50,808 --> 00:42:53,148
♪In the fire you rise again♪

768
00:42:53,216 --> 00:42:55,482
♪You made it through the worst♪

769
00:42:55,842 --> 00:42:57,920
♪The best is yet to come♪

770
00:42:58,169 --> 00:43:00,339
♪The best is yet to come♪

771
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,192
♪Isn't it magical♪

772
00:43:04,192 --> 00:43:07,838
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

773
00:43:07,872 --> 00:43:09,728
♪And I see them sparkling♪

774
00:43:09,952 --> 00:43:12,083
♪Nobody knows♪

775
00:43:12,704 --> 00:43:14,614
♪What tomorrow brings♪

776
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,203
♪You made it through the worst♪

777
00:43:17,390 --> 00:43:19,598
♪The best is yet to come♪

778
00:43:19,885 --> 00:43:22,034
♪The best is yet to come♪

779
00:43:22,330 --> 00:43:23,744
♪Isn't it magical♪

780
00:43:23,744 --> 00:43:25,956
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

781
00:43:26,030 --> 00:43:28,384
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

782
00:43:28,384 --> 00:43:29,472
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

783
00:43:29,472 --> 00:43:32,923
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

784
00:43:33,376 --> 00:43:35,650
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

785
00:43:36,064 --> 00:43:36,928
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

786
00:43:36,928 --> 00:43:38,448
♪Isn't it magical♪
